This page documents the '''game mechanics formulas''' in '''[[Soul Blazer]]''' (SNES).

==Overview==
Soul Blazer uses several mathematical formulas to calculate damage, experience, and other game values. All calculations use integer math with truncation (no rounding).

==Damage Formulas==

===Physical Damage===
Player attacking an enemy:
<pre>
Damage = ATK - (DEF ÷ 2)
Minimum = 1

Where:
  ATK = Player Attack (Base + Sword)
  DEF = Enemy Defense
</pre>

